                                                          <p>A one-sided love is like a slow-acting poison—you know it&#039;s tearing you apart, yet you can&#039;t stop coming back for more. For 5 years and 120 days, Jung Dahee has been hopelessly devoted to her childhood friend, Lee Beomseok. Rejection has become such a regular part of her life that she almost expects it, but she&#039;s determined to change her fate with one final, heartfelt confession on the day of the CSAT. Everything was supposed to go according to plan. Until she accidentally discovers a shocking secret: the boy she&#039;s loved for years is having an affair with none other than her own older sister.

